    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-02T19:00:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">690D.91/9–2851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 2, 1951—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>171. Re: Kashmir (<gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss>s 389, 390, Sept
                        28):<note n="1" xml:id="d242fn1">See footnotes 2 and 3, <ref
                            target="#pg_1868">p. 1868</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Re pos course of action:</hi> Dept strongly supports <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> belief UK–US cld draft res based on both Arts
                    36 and 37 without citing them. Dept believes continued ref these arts has been
                    somewhat confusing. While must await Graham report and private discussions with
                    him, Dept considering fol course:</p>
                <p>Expand Graham’s powers enable him endeavor induce parties carry out his 13 point
                    program previously submitted to parties. Dept favorably disposed <gloss
                        target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> belief res shld both hold parties <gloss
                        target="#t_UNCIP1">UNCIP</gloss> commitments and enable Graham explore
                    mutually acceptable settlements <pb facs="0410" n="1874" xml:id="pg_1874"/>
                    along lines Dixon’s powers. Phrasing can probably be found to avoid implication
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> abandoning <gloss target="#t_UNCIP1"
                        >UNCIP</gloss> agreements while seeking solution <hi rend="italic">mutually
                        acceptable both parties</hi>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
